At the end of the day, after hearing Nasir out, Ravi became so inspired to share this newly acquired wisdom with everyone else. Ravi promised his friend that he would share this priceless knowledge with others so that people could understand the laws of wealth. Soon, he constructed an enormous wooden tablet with all these precious rules carved upon it. That’s why we can learn and apply Babylon’s timeless laws of wealth even today.

Most importantly, this story shows us that anyone can become rich when they are determined and consistent about it. All it takes is to follow, step by step, the laws that regulate wealth accumulation. Start by saving at least 10% of your income for yourself. You can deposit it or keep it in your mattress but always spare 1/10 of your monthly earnings. If you have saved enough, start investing in sustainable and reputable businesses that return dividends, then make do with your debts. Never sign up for get-rich-quick schemes. Instead, invest in yourself and protect your fortune with diversification and insurance.

Learning to become rich is hard work. It never happens overnight. To embark upon this exciting journey, you must be prepared to make mistakes and accept the consequences. Also, remember that risk is noble, but no one is impervious to failure. You can lose nearly all of your possessions at some point, but that doesn’t mean you should stop trying.

Try this

One way to start saving more is to revise your expenses. We believe we need many things to have comfortable and well-rounded lives, but do we? Here are several techniques to help you audit your budget seriously :

• Divide all your spending into categories;
• Update your earnings and expenses. All the numbers need to be on paper, not in your head;
• Eliminate all unnecessary spending;
• Come up with new financial goals.
